page.title: 08Wykeham Trees Limited
page.content: Trees have always been of the greatest importance at Wykeham, both in terms of forestrey and making the area more pleasent.With a private house set in landscaped parkland and accompanying farms and woodland tree production has been a continuous process for many years. The Nursery Book goes back to 1862. Extra heavy trees for amenity have been grown in association with Exbury Trees 1973. They have developed ablend of practical experiance and modern techniques in the production of trees of the highest quality. In 1978 they increased their plantings in response to the views of customers from Southern England to the north of Scotland who preferred to plant trees grown in northern locations.
